                                <cell><m>-1000</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>2.9940\ldots</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>-2000</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>2.9970\ldots</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>-3000</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>2.9980\ldots</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>-4000</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>2.9985\ldots</m></cell>
                            </row>
                        </tabular>
                    </table>
                </sidebyside>

                <p>Thus for really large positive <m>x</m> and for really large negative <m>x</m>, we see that the function values get closer and closer to <m>y=3</m>. (This is referred to as the horizontal asymptote, and will be graphed as a dashed horizontal line on the graph of this function.)</p>

                <p>Putting all of this together, we can sketch a graph of this function.</p>

